observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

provide the necessary support in enjoining the remaining barangays to establish their own MRF and to strictly implement waste segregation at source; 
strictly enforce and intensify the information campaign on the no-littering policy among the residents;
develop and operate a sanitary landfill as a final disposal site for solid and, eventually, residual wastes of the Municipality; and 
strictly comply with all other prescribed procedures and guidelines under RA No. 9003.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Agriculturist to:

conduct investigation on the circumstances surrounding the death of the animals and determine if negligence was committed so that the concerned recipients may be compelled to refund the cost of animals as part of their responsibility, pursuant to the Animal Dispersal Contract;
improve the existing system of documentation by maintaining a logbook or record for easy tracking of next-in-line recipients to ensure effective accomplishment of the program;
submit timely Livestock Death Certificate to the Municipal Accountant to support the dropping from the books the cost of dead animals in accordance with the rules and regulations for the relief from accountability; and
conduct a more intensive monitoring and evaluation of the project implementation to determine the success or failure of the program for further decision making.

